"what quality is shared by all objects that provoke our aesthetic emotions? what quality is common to sta. sophia and the windows at chartres, mexican sculpture, a persian bowl, a pair of air jordans, chinese carpets, pleasures streetwear, and the masterpieces of poussin, piero della francesca, and cézanne? only one answer seems possible — significant form. in each, lines and colours combined in a particular way, certain forms and relations of forms, stir our aesthetic emotions." -clive bell, 1913.

both my parents were photographers in their younger years. they owned a little photo studio where they would shoot quinceañeras and weddings. i guess part of their agenda as parents was to motivate my siblings and i to appreciate what they did for a living, so when i was five my mom gave me a disposable camera. this is a picture i took from the first roll of film i ever shot using said camera.
